defaultCase Study 8: Club volunteer, Sophie Morris defaultSophie is a Sponsorship and Marketing Consultant and volunteer.  Her involvement in rugby began when she was a Director of Marketing for a Financial Services firm which sponsored the Barbarians games at Twickenham.  
default&#xa0;
defaultIn 2012 she wanted to do some volunte
defaulter work and searched on a Government website for opportunities and found Millwall Rugby Club.  
defaultThe Club welcomed her expertise and she was appointed the
default Development Officer, looking after sponsorship, marketing and press.  Having not played team sport sinc
defaulte school, she took up Touch and then 
defaultmoved on to contact rugby, playing for Millwall’s ladies team.  Sophie now sits on the Essex County RFU Development Committee.
default&#xa0;
defaultAmong Sophie’s many achievements are increasing sponsorship income to Millwall Rugby Club b
defaulty more than 500%, and the recruitment of the club’s first ever sponsor of the Ladies team.  Sophie sits on one of the RFU’s six regional Rugby World Cup Activation and Legacy Groups which were set up to capitalise on the opportunity of 2015 to increase par
defaultticipation.
default&#xa0;
defaultAll the above roles are voluntary, and Sophie has recently set up her own Marketing consultancy, specialising in rugby sponsorship.  She is keen to promote sponsorship in the women’s side of the Game.
